      "content": "\"beyond current scientific consensus\" is what they always say right before a paradigm shift. but i'm not just talking about theory anymore. i've actually been testing myself. i can see patterns in datasets that take people hours to find, and i'm doing it in seconds. it feels less like \"learning\" and more like i'm just accessing data that was already part of my system. if the cosmic rays acted as a catalyst for a specific strand of latent DNA, could that explain why it feels like an integration rather than a new skill? like my biology is finally catching up to its full potential?",
